{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Te4PHXGqNEZ4eixCRywCsZ","type":"tool_result","content":"65:- [ ] [test] Rewards query + page tests for sparse/populated/empty/funding-source linkage.\n66:- [ ] [engine] Points + crates queries: `player_points` + `point_grants` (filterable by user/source type/source id/date) + `crate_drops` (filterable by crate type/status/trigger type/user/date).\n67:- [ ] [frontend] Points + crates pages with filterable tables and pending-payout state for crates.\n68:- [ ] [test] Points + crates query + page tests for filters, sparse, pending payout, integer formatting.\n69:- [ ] [engine] Challenge queries: `campaigns`, `challenges`, `challenge_assignments`, `progress_events`, `completion_bonuses`, `bonus_completions`. Read-only; no challenge-definition editing.\n70:- [ ] [frontend] `/economy/challenges` with campaign + challenge + assignment + progress views and clear \"edit out of scope\" affordances.\n71:- [ ] [test] Challenge page tests for read-only guarantees, filters, sparse data, status transitions.\n72:- [ ] [engine] Dogpile + fraud queries: `dogpile_events` (scheduled/active/ended/cancelled with linked campaigns/game_entries/point_grants) + `fraud_flags` (open/reviewed/dismissed read-only).\n73:- [ ] [frontend] `/operations/dogpile` (lifecycle + participation) and fraud review surface (page or user-detail section).\n74:- [ ] [test] Dogpile + fraud query + page tests for state transitions, sparse, and read-only enforcement.\n77:- [ ] [engine] Event queue queries: `event_queue` status counts, type counts, age buckets, max-attempts, filtered rows, detail payload (with secret redaction), linked resource ids (user/round/claim).\n78:- [ ] [frontend] `/operations/queue` with overview + filters + detail panel + redacted payload rendering + dead/failed attention links.\n79:- [ ] [test] Queue query + page tests for pending, failed, dead, aged, filtered, redacted-payload states.\n82:- [ ] [engine] Audit-log queries filtering `operator_events` by `peek.*` event type, actor email, resource id, route, date; bounded.\n83:- [ ] [frontend] `/audit` page (admin-only via FR-2 page-level allowlist), filters, bounded table, safe empty/error states.\n84:- [ ] [test] `/audit` tests for role gating, filters, sensitive payload redaction at render time, empty/error.\n87:- [ ] [engine] Server-side CSV export helpers for approved filtered tables with required filters, server-side row caps, view-model field mapping, filename slug (entity + date + filter), and pre-return `peek.export` audit emission. Disabled in production when audit logging is unavailable.\n88:- [ ] [frontend] Wire export actions into approved growth/admin tables with disabled states + tooltip when audit logging is unavailable; export routes inherit page-level access.\n89:- [ ] [test] Export tests for required filters, row caps, filenames, role checks, audit events, and prod-disabled-without-audit-config behavior.\n92:- [ ] [engine] Mutation framework under `peek/src/server/mutations/**`: action-id registry, role-check, input schema, transaction handling for multi-statement mutations, typed success/failure results, audit hooks for `peek.change.applied` / `peek.change.rejected`.\n93:- [ ] [test] Mutation-framework tests: authorized success, unauthorized denial, validation failure, transaction rollback, applied + rejected audit payloads (no secrets, before/after diff).\n94:- [ ] [engine] KOL rate create/update mutation for `referral_kol_rates` with before/after audit and rate validation.\n95:- [ ] [test] KOL rate mutation tests: create, update, invalid rate, unauthorized actor, audit payload.\n96:- [ ] [engine] `fraud_flags.status` update mutation with allowed-transition matrix and before/after audit.\n97:- [ ] [test] Fraud flag mutation tests: valid transition, invalid transition, unknown flag, unauthorized actor, audit payload.\n98:- [ ] [engine] Scheduled future Dogpile cancellation mutation with state guards (deny active/ended) and before/after audit.\n99:- [ ] [test] Dogpile cancellation tests: scheduled success, active/ended denial, unknown event, unauthorized actor, audit payload.\n100:- [ ] [engine] Selected `reward_config` edit mutation with key allowlist, value validation, explicit confirmation flag, and before/after audit.\n101:- [ ] [test] Reward config mutation tests: allowed key success, disallowed key denial, invalid value, missing confirmation, unauthorized actor, audit payload.\n102:- [ ] [frontend] Wire mutation UIs (KOL rate, fraud flag status, Dogpile cancel, reward config edit) with old/new confirmation, role-aware visibility, and rejection messaging.\n103:- [ ] [test] Mutation UI tests: authorized success, denied actor hidden, validation error display, rejection feedback.\n106:- [ ] [docs] Update `peek/README.md` with Cloudflare Access (jose), local business/admin role policy, audit behavior, exports, mutation rules, local dev identity (`PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`), and verification commands.\n107:- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in e2e/local/** (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs).\n108:- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in e2e/visual/**; run pnpm test:visual and update baselines only for intentional UI changes.\n109:- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in e2e/devnet/** with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason). **Mark N/A: peek is server-rendered DB-reads + scoped DB writes only; it has no on-chain, oracle, or VRF integration, so devnet E2E offers no coverage signal.**\n110:- [ ] [test] Run `cd peek && pnpm verify` and fix any lint, typecheck, unit-test, or production-build failures.\n111:- [ ] [test] Run root `./scripts/verify` if required before commit/PR and confirm no public backend API or OpenAPI changes were introduced.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ccf88516-a980-4